Beauty Salon Website

Overview

The Beauty Salon Website is a modern, responsive web application designed to showcase salon services, facilitate online appointment bookings, and provide an enhanced user experience for clients. It is built with a user-friendly interface and a visually appealing design to attract and retain customers.

Features

Home Page: Engaging introduction with high-quality images and a welcoming message.

About Us: Detailed information about the salon, mission, and team members.

Services: Comprehensive list of beauty and spa services with pricing.

Booking System: Online appointment scheduling with availability checks.

Gallery: Showcase of previous work and salon ambiance.

Testimonials: Customer reviews and feedback.

Contact Page: Contact form, address, and social media links.

Blog: Articles on beauty tips and trends (optional).

Technologies Used

Frontend: HTML, CSS, JavaScript (React/Angular/Vue for dynamic UI)

Backend: Node.js with Express / PHP / Python (Django/Flask)

Database: MySQL / PostgreSQL / MongoDB

Styling: Bootstrap / Tailwind CSS

Authentication: Firebase / JWT / OAuth (for user accounts and bookings)

Hosting: AWS / Netlify / Vercel / Heroku

Installation

Clone the repository:

git clone https://github.com/your-repo/beauty-salon-website.git
cd beauty-salon-website

Install dependencies:

npm install  # For Node.js projects

Start the development server:

npm start  # or npm run dev

Deployment

Build the project:

npm run build

Deploy to hosting service (e.g., Netlify, Vercel, AWS).

Contributing

Fork the repository.

Create a new branch:

git checkout -b feature-branch

Commit your changes:

git commit -m "Added new feature"

